    <para id="id1167311581669">
      <emphasis effect="bold">1.10.2.1. METALS (</emphasis>
      <emphasis effect="italics">with special reference to the mobility of conducting electrons and its implications for particle accelerators</emphasis>
      <emphasis effect="bold">).</emphasis>
    </para>
    <para id="id1167315839947"><emphasis effect="bold"/>Metal is a lattice of positive ions held together by a gas of conducting electrons. The conducting electrons belonging to the conduction band have their wave-functions spread through out the metallic lattice. The average kinetic energy per electron is (3/5)E<sub>F</sub> (This will be a tutorial exercise). Hence </para>
